> Is there anything more satisfying than chicken wings? Survey says: No! This combination
> comes with two of our favorite wing flavors: one seasoned with savory Cajun-style spices
> and the other with zingy Buffalo spice rub and a touch of brown sugar. Once baked,
> these wings are perfectly crispy on the outside and super juicy on the inside. The only
> question is what you'll dip them in!

> Keep frozen or refrigerated until ready to eat; best if used within 7 days.

> If frozen, thaw in the refrigerator (at 40 degrees) overnight or at room temperature
> for 2-3 hours before reheating.

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat #oven to 425 degrees.

Place @Cajun Chicken Wings{18%ounce} and @Buffalo Chicken Wings{18%ounce} on a lightly
oiled, foil-lined #baking sheet{}. Bake on middle rack for ~{15%minutes}.

Flip wings and cook until lightly browned and crispy, ~{10%minutes} more.